window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Nothing they do can fix me. I'm beyond repair.</b></p> <p>Life at Bainbridge Hall is everything I feared it would be, yet these bastards have me in a chokehold. With each passing day, I struggle with my growing affection for them. The lines I drew in the beginning have begun to blur.</p> <p>I should've left… back before feelings were involved.</p> <p>From the moment I met them, I was intrigued, but nothing about our situation is simple. Every time they touch me, another broken piece is mended. And now, everything I want is wrapped up in three unruly men.</p> <p>One troubled brawler. One damaged heart. And one bleeding soul.</p> <p>Bear. Duke. Mason.</p> <p>The closer we become, the more I want to lean on their strength. But I can't possibly burden them with the past that haunts me—even if they believe repairing my shattered pieces will make us whole.</p> <p>Bainbridge Hall. They may not be the villains of my nightmares, but they are definitely the bastards of my dreams.</p> <p>Bear <i>is the second book in the Bastards of Bainbridge Hall trilogy, centering around three men and one woman. For mature listeners.</i></p>"; 
